The twitterWebhook python source is located at '/usr/local/src/twitterWebhook' and
the init.d script is '/etc/init.d/twitterWebhook'.

'setup.sh' 
- moves files to correct directories
- sets the file permissions and
- configures 'twitterWebhook' to run on boot

DOCKER instructions
1. after building on the host system save immage
    docker save -o e:/Jupyter/alarmMonitor/alarm.tar alarm
2. copy image to RPi
    rsync -avz alarm.tar pi@192.168.0.4:/home/pi/alarmMonitor
3. on RPi load impage
    docker load -i alarm.tar
4. RUN
    docker run --name=alarm --device=/dev/ttyUSB0 -it -p 80:80 -p 443:443 alarm:latest
